					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The reason there are borders is that the default scaling modes (1X, 2X, 3X) scale all pixels equally, so that you don't have some lines of pixels thicker than others in an erratic uneven mess.<br /><br />Unfortunately, I don't see an option for what you want in Nestopia. You can stretch to the full screen, or you can do 1X/2X/3X. Independently from this, you can also adjust the aspect ratio to be either square pixels or &quot;TV aspect&quot;.<br /><br />Edit: oh wait, hang on, there it is.<br /><br />In the view menu under screen size, choose MAX and also TV Aspect. Does that do what you want?</div>

